1
00:00:01,936 --> 00:00:03,402
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i> THE PRETENDER.    


2
00:00:03,470 --> 00:00:06,938
WHO AM I?                       
WAS I BOUGHT OR WAS I STOLEN?   
WHERE ARE MY MOM AND DAD?       


3
00:00:07,007 --> 00:00:11,109
            <i> IT WAS MY FAULT.</i>   
            <i> I SHOULD BE THE ONE</i>
            <i> LYING IN THAT BED.</i> 


4
00:00:11,178 --> 00:00:14,045
        MR. RAINES, JAROD HAS   
        BEEN HARDER TO CATCH    
        THAN WE THOUGHT.        


5
00:00:14,114 --> 00:00:18,684
BRING JAROD BACK,               
OR I'LL GET SOMEONE WHO WILL.   


6
00:00:18,752 --> 00:00:20,218
    ARE WE CLEAR?               


7
00:00:57,491 --> 00:01:00,225
            [ Ringing ]         


8
00:01:34,794 --> 00:01:38,363
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>HERE'S YOUR KEY, SIR.</i>           
<i>YOU'RE IN ROOM 323.</i>             


9
00:01:38,431 --> 00:01:40,432
                <i> [ Bell Dings ]</i> 


10
00:01:42,936 --> 00:01:45,370
<i>[ Loud Clattering ]</i>             


11
00:01:45,439 --> 00:01:49,207
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>HELP ME. HELP ME.</i>               


12
00:01:54,815 --> 00:01:56,815
                HELLO?          


13
00:02:00,654 --> 00:02:02,654
                <i> [ Door Closes ]</i>


14
00:02:09,563 --> 00:02:12,164
            HELLO. HELLO?       


15
00:02:15,535 --> 00:02:18,270
    IS THERE ANYBODY HERE?      


16
00:02:18,339 --> 00:02:20,805
            HELP ME. HELP ME.   


17
00:02:20,874 --> 00:02:23,308
        [ Panting ]             


18
00:02:23,377 --> 00:02:26,077
                            SIR?


19
00:02:27,714 --> 00:02:30,482
            DON'T YOU DIE ON ME.
            [ Blows ]           


20
00:02:36,223 --> 00:02:39,925
    <i> DON'T YOU DIE ON ME,</i>       
    <i> DAMN IT!</i>                   


21
00:02:41,895 --> 00:02:43,728
            DON'T DIE.          


22
00:02:45,031 --> 00:02:48,066
            COME ON. WAKE UP.   
             COME ON.           


23
00:03:05,752 --> 00:03:08,253
                [ Woman ]       
                FRONT DESK.     
                CAN I HELP YOU? 


24
00:03:09,657 --> 00:03:11,623
                <i> NO. NEVER MIND.</i>


25
00:03:58,205 --> 00:04:02,106
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>               


26
00:04:06,747 --> 00:04:09,781
        - YEAH.                 
        - I'M DOWNSTAIRS.       


27
00:04:09,850 --> 00:04:11,783
    WE GONNA DO THIS HIT?       


28
00:04:11,851 --> 00:04:13,952
        HIT?                    
DON'T JERK ME AROUND.           


29
00:04:14,021 --> 00:04:16,755
    WE GOTTA TAKE               
    THIS GUY OUT TODAY.         
    ARE YOU IN OR OUT?          


30
00:04:28,535 --> 00:04:31,003
- I'M IN.                       
- HOW AM I GONNA RECOGNIZE YOU? 


31
00:04:37,911 --> 00:04:39,844
        I HAVE A LIMP.          


32
00:04:41,114 --> 00:04:44,616
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>               


33
00:05:29,596 --> 00:05:32,931
<i>MISS PARKER IS TRYING</i>           
<i>TO QUIT SMOKING? HOW?</i>           


34
00:05:32,999 --> 00:05:36,768
        NICOTINE PATCH.         
        PERSONALLY, I CAN ONLY  
        APPLAUD THAT RESOLVE.   


35
00:05:36,837 --> 00:05:40,405
<i>SYDNEY, RESOLVE IS ONE THING,</i>   
<i>BUT HOMICIDE IS ANOTHER.</i>        


36
00:05:43,610 --> 00:05:47,111
I JUST GOT WORD                 
JAROD MADE CONTACT?             


37
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:50,081
    - HOW ARE YOU FEELING?      
    - GUESS.                    


38
00:05:50,150 --> 00:05:52,817
[ Clears Throat ]               
OKAY.                           


39
00:05:52,886 --> 00:05:55,386
WE GOT A HIGH-PRIORITY          
E-MAIL FROM JAROD,              


40
00:05:55,455 --> 00:05:57,622
BUT IT WAS ADDRESSED            
TO SYDNEY.                      


41
00:05:57,691 --> 00:06:00,959
    - PUT IT ON THE SCREEN.     
    - IT WAS TAGGED "PERSONAL." 


42
00:06:01,027 --> 00:06:04,462
    - ON THE SCREEN!            
    - IT'S ALL RIGHT, BROOTS.   


43
00:06:04,531 --> 00:06:07,365
        I DON'T HAVE ANY SECRETS
        FROM MISS PARKER.       


44
00:06:15,409 --> 00:06:18,443
HAVEN'T YOU EVER SEEN           
ANYONE CHEW GUM BEFORE?         


45
00:06:23,050 --> 00:06:27,084
    <i> "SYDNEY, YOU'RE EXPECTED</i>   
     <i> AT THE TWIN CITIES HOTEL</i>  
     <i> IN MINNEAPOLIS, MINNESOTA,</i>


46
00:06:27,154 --> 00:06:30,455
<i>"ON THE 22nd</i>                    
<i> FOR A VERY SPECIAL GATHERING.</i>  


47
00:06:30,523 --> 00:06:32,456
<i>MAY HOLD KEY TO THE PAST.</i>       
<i>JAROD."</i>                         


48
00:06:32,525 --> 00:06:35,994
<i>THE 22nd IS TODAY.</i>              
<i>WHO ELSE KNOWS ABOUT THIS?</i>      


49
00:06:36,062 --> 00:06:40,065
- UH, NO ONE.                   
- CAN YOU GET THE CORPORATE JET 
  READY FOR TAKEOFF?            


50
00:06:41,168 --> 00:06:44,869
                MINNEAPOLIS.    
                ONE PASSENGER.  


51
00:06:44,937 --> 00:06:46,937
ONE?                            


52
00:06:47,006 --> 00:06:49,140
            WELL, THE MESSAGE   
            WAS FOR ME.         


53
00:06:49,209 --> 00:06:54,145
WELL, WHEN IT COMES TO JAROD,   
THERE IS NO "ME," ONLY "US."    


54
00:06:54,214 --> 00:06:56,214
    OH.                         


55
00:07:02,122 --> 00:07:05,156
        MAKE IT TWO PASSENGERS. 


56
00:07:05,225 --> 00:07:08,760
TAKE THIS. YOU'LL NEED IT.      


57
00:07:10,197 --> 00:07:13,198
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>WE'RE AROUND BACK.</i>              
<i>WE'LL MEET YOU IN THE ALLEY.</i>    


58
00:07:18,505 --> 00:07:20,638
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>CHECK YOU ALL OUT FRONT.</i>        


59
00:07:29,382 --> 00:07:32,984
YOU DON'T LOOK LIKE             
NO STONE KILLER TO ME.          


60
00:07:33,052 --> 00:07:36,388
            WELL, LOOKS         
            AREN'T EVERYTHING.  


61
00:07:45,432 --> 00:07:49,500
<i>[ Mock British Accent ]</i>         
<i>YES, I'D LIKE TO HAVE A CARTON</i>  
<i>OF MENTHOL CIGARETTES...</i>        


62
00:07:49,569 --> 00:07:53,171
WAITING ON HER PILLOW FOR HER   
FOR WHEN SHE ARRIVES.           


63
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:58,243
UH, YES, THE NAME IS PARKER,    
MISS PARKER.                    


64
00:07:58,312 --> 00:08:00,878
OH! JOLLY GOOD.                 
THAT WOULD BE LOVELY.           


65
00:08:00,948 --> 00:08:02,880
    REALLY.                     
    [ Chuckling ]               


66
00:08:02,950 --> 00:08:05,917
    WELL, THANK YOU.            
    VERY GOOD.                  


67
00:08:05,986 --> 00:08:07,986
        CHEERS.                 


68
00:08:09,288 --> 00:08:12,857
        [ Wheezing Laugh ]      


69
00:08:12,926 --> 00:08:14,926
                <i> [ Phone Rings ]</i>
    [ Clears Throat ]           


70
00:08:14,994 --> 00:08:16,994
    [ British Accent ]          
    BROOTS HERE.                


71
00:08:18,899 --> 00:08:22,467
MR. RAINES? UH, SIR.            


72
00:08:22,536 --> 00:08:25,703
SECUR--                         
S-S-SECURITY SITUATION?         


73
00:08:27,307 --> 00:08:30,608
UH, NO, I DON'T, UH--           
I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING...        


74
00:08:30,677 --> 00:08:33,912
ABOUT ANY, UH, TRANSMISSIONS    
CONCER-- CONCERNING JAROD.      


75
00:08:41,922 --> 00:08:43,922
            <i> COME ON IN.</i>        


76
00:08:47,260 --> 00:08:51,095
HOW YOU DOIN'?                  
COME ON OVER. HAVE A SEAT.      


77
00:08:51,164 --> 00:08:53,098
                    I'LL STAND. 


78
00:08:53,166 --> 00:08:55,266
            MR. BEAULIEU        
            OFFERED YOU A CHAIR.


79
00:08:55,335 --> 00:08:57,735
        HUSH UP, DONNY.         


80
00:08:57,804 --> 00:08:59,871
<i>YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO</i>            
<i>FORGIVE MY NEPHEW.</i>              


81
00:08:59,940 --> 00:09:02,573
<i>HE'S YOUNG.</i>                     
<i> HE'S JUST FULL OF THE DEVIL.</i>   


82
00:09:04,210 --> 00:09:07,111
YOU EVER SUCK A CRAWFISH,       
MR., UH--                       


83
00:09:07,180 --> 00:09:09,781
                    DOE.        


84
00:09:09,849 --> 00:09:11,816
                    JAROD DOE.  


85
00:09:11,885 --> 00:09:13,818
            NOT THAT I RECALL.  


86
00:09:13,887 --> 00:09:18,757
WELL, IT'S REAL SIMPLE.         
YOU JUST RIP THE HEAD OFF       
LIKE THAT AND SUCK.             


87
00:09:18,825 --> 00:09:22,160
            I'D LIKE TO GET     
            THIS OVER WITH AS   
            QUICKLY AS POSSIBLE.


88
00:09:24,030 --> 00:09:26,831
WELL, I ADMIRE YOUR CANDOR,     
MR. DOE.                        


89
00:09:26,899 --> 00:09:30,301
AIN'T ENOUGH OF IT              
IN THE WORLD TO SUIT ME.        


90
00:09:30,370 --> 00:09:32,870
REASON YOU WAS HIRED...         


91
00:09:32,939 --> 00:09:35,740
WAS YOU HAVE NO PAST CONNECTIONS
HERE IN NEW ORLEANS.            


92
00:09:35,808 --> 00:09:37,809
NOBODY KNOWS YOUR FACE.         


93
00:09:37,877 --> 00:09:42,380
THIS, IN TURN, GIVES YOU        
NO FUTURE CONNECTIONS TO ME.    


94
00:09:42,449 --> 00:09:46,851
NOW THE WORD IS,                
YOU'RE CLEAN AND DISCREET,      


95
00:09:49,656 --> 00:09:52,990
EXCEPT FOR THAT...              
PICTURE-TAKING BUSINESS.        


96
00:09:53,059 --> 00:09:57,262
    GUY WHACKS PEOPLE           
    AND TAKES SNAPSHOTS?        
    WHAT'S THAT ABOUT?          


97
00:10:00,066 --> 00:10:03,935
        YOUR BUSINESS           
        IS YOUR BUSINESS,       


98
00:10:04,003 --> 00:10:05,937
            MINE'S MINE.        


99
00:10:07,507 --> 00:10:10,341
I WANT YOU TO KNOW              
THE FACT THAT YOU'RE            
A CRIPPLE, UH,                  


100
00:10:10,410 --> 00:10:12,877
HAS NO EFFECT                   
ON MY CONFIDENCE IN YOU.        


101
00:10:12,945 --> 00:10:15,546
        THAT'S VERY GENEROUS.   


102
00:10:15,615 --> 00:10:18,850
MAYBE IF YOU HANG AROUND,       
WE CAN GET YOU A SPECIAL PARKING
PLACE IN FRONT OF THE CLUB.     


103
00:10:18,919 --> 00:10:21,653
<i>[ Chuckles ]</i>                    


104
00:10:28,461 --> 00:10:31,062
THIS OLD BOY'S NAME             
IS BENJAMIN WORTH.              


105
00:10:31,130 --> 00:10:33,632
HIS ADDRESS                     
IS ON THE BACK.                 


106
00:10:35,102 --> 00:10:37,067
    WHY DO YOU WANT HIM KILLED? 


107
00:10:37,136 --> 00:10:41,139
YOUR BUSINESS IS YOUR BUSINESS, 
AND MINE'S MINE.                


108
00:10:44,143 --> 00:10:46,444
TWENTY-FIVE THOUSAND NOW,       


109
00:10:46,513 --> 00:10:48,680
AND 25,000 WHEN IT'S DONE.      


110
00:10:48,748 --> 00:10:51,415
AFTER CONFIRMATION              
OF WORTH'S DEATH,               


111
00:10:51,484 --> 00:10:54,418
YOU'LL GET IDENTIFICATION       
OF A SECOND TARGET.             


112
00:10:54,487 --> 00:10:57,054
            SECOND TARGET?      


113
00:10:57,123 --> 00:10:59,190
        SAME DEAL.              


114
00:10:59,259 --> 00:11:02,360
<i>I'M GONNA SEND</i>                  
<i>DONNY HERE WITH YOU...</i>          


115
00:11:02,429 --> 00:11:07,065
<i>TO ACT AS MY EYES AND EARS.</i>     


116
00:11:07,134 --> 00:11:10,334
    HAVE YOU GOT A PROBLEM      
    WITH THAT OR SOMETHING?     


117
00:11:10,404 --> 00:11:14,205
<i>'CAUSE IF YOU DO,</i>               
<i>I CAN MAKE A PHONE CALL</i>         
<i>AND GET SOMEBODY ELSE IN HERE.</i>  


118
00:11:15,808 --> 00:11:18,877
                NO PROBLEM.     


119
00:11:18,945 --> 00:11:20,745
                I'M YOUR MAN.   


120
00:11:20,814 --> 00:11:23,314
            YEAH,               
            I KNOW YOU ARE.     


121
00:11:33,626 --> 00:11:37,628
[ Clears Throat ]               
WHAT'S THIS?                    


122
00:11:37,697 --> 00:11:40,731
            I NEED FILM.        
GO TO A DRUGSTORE.              


123
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:44,568
        HIGH-SPEED, S.G.R. 3200,
        BLACK AND WHITE.        


124
00:11:44,637 --> 00:11:46,638
            FOR MY SNAPSHOTS.   


125
00:11:46,706 --> 00:11:49,107
    WHERE THE HELL AM I         
    SUPPOSED TO FIND IT?        


126
00:11:49,176 --> 00:11:53,310
        THAT'S NOT MY PROBLEM.  
        PICK ME UP IN MY HOTEL  
        IN THREE HOURS.         


127
00:11:53,379 --> 00:11:57,114
<i>MY INSTINCTS SAY JAROD</i>          
<i>WOULDN'T HAVE BROUGHT ME HERE</i>   
<i>WITHOUT A REASON.</i>               


128
00:11:57,183 --> 00:11:59,784
        I DON'T CARE            
        ABOUT YOUR INSTINCTS.   


129
00:11:59,852 --> 00:12:03,087
THIS WHOLE THING IS JUST ANOTHER
ONE OF JAROD'S SNIPE HUNTS.     


130
00:12:03,156 --> 00:12:06,157
            <i> [ Phone Rings ]</i>    
            [ Sighs ]           


131
00:12:08,961 --> 00:12:10,895
                WHAT?           


132
00:12:10,964 --> 00:12:13,465
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?            
I'VE BEEN TRYING TO REACH YOU.  


133
00:12:13,533 --> 00:12:16,301
BROOTS, CALM DOWN.              
        LISTEN, RAINES KNOWS.   


134
00:12:16,369 --> 00:12:18,903
    - KNOWS WHAT?               
    - ABOUT THE TRANSMISSION    
      FROM JAROD.               


135
00:12:18,972 --> 00:12:20,738
                DID YOU TELL HIM
                WHERE WE ARE?   


136
00:12:20,807 --> 00:12:24,275
NO! IT'S JUST A MATTER OF TIME  
BEFORE HE COMES DOWN HERE       
AND HE'S SNOOPING AROUND.       


137
00:12:24,344 --> 00:12:26,444
YOU KNOW, HE'S GOT              
THIS PLACE WIRED.               


138
00:12:26,512 --> 00:12:28,780
        BROOTS, WHERE ARE YOU   
        CALLING FROM?           


139
00:12:34,487 --> 00:12:37,188
            [ Disgusted Sigh ]  
            MUTANT.             


140
00:12:37,256 --> 00:12:40,157
IS THERE A PROBLEM?             
            ISN'T THERE ALWAYS? 


141
00:12:59,545 --> 00:13:02,179
    WHAT THE HELL IS GOING ON?  


142
00:13:05,151 --> 00:13:08,352
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>I THINK I KNOW WHY WE'RE HERE.</i>  


143
00:13:19,933 --> 00:13:23,167
<i>IT'S ONLY BEEN</i>                  
<i>ON THE MARKET THREE WEEKS.</i>      


144
00:13:23,236 --> 00:13:26,804
THE PLUMBING'S SHOT,            
AND IT NEEDS                    
A NEW COAT OF PAINT,            


145
00:13:26,873 --> 00:13:30,508
BUT YOU WON'T FIND              
A SAFER NEIGHBORHOOD            
IN NEW ORLEANS.                 


146
00:13:30,576 --> 00:13:32,710
            IT SEEMS VERY NICE. 


147
00:13:32,779 --> 00:13:37,148
ARE YOU FROM                    
THE REAL ESTATE COMPANY?        
        UH, NO, MA'AM, I'M NOT. 


148
00:13:42,355 --> 00:13:47,692
ACTUALLY, MA'AM, I REPRESENT    
A VINTAGE AUTOMOBILE HOUSE      
IN BATON ROUGE.                 


149
00:13:47,761 --> 00:13:50,928
I WAS WONDERING--               
DO YOU KNOW THIS MAN?           


150
00:13:50,996 --> 00:13:53,831
                SONNY HERBERT.  


151
00:13:53,900 --> 00:13:56,868
            I HAVEN'T SEEN HIM  
            IN NEARLY 25 YEARS. 


152
00:13:56,936 --> 00:14:01,505
I'M INTERESTED IN THE CAR       
THAT HE'S LEANING ON.           
            HIS PRIDE AND JOY.  


153
00:14:01,574 --> 00:14:03,608
        HE USED TO LIVE HERE.   


154
00:14:03,676 --> 00:14:06,544
            HE HAD AN OFFICE    
            DOWN IN FAT CITY.   


155
00:14:06,612 --> 00:14:09,446
                I DON'T REMEMBER
                EXACTLY WHERE.  


156
00:14:09,515 --> 00:14:13,350
    I CAN STILL SEE ALL THOSE   
    PHOTOGRAPHS HE HAD PINNED UP
    AROUND HIS ROOM.            


157
00:14:13,419 --> 00:14:15,586
PHOTOGRAPHS?                    
                    OF THE KIDS.


158
00:14:15,655 --> 00:14:18,722
        MR. HERBERT WAS         
        A PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR. 


159
00:14:18,791 --> 00:14:21,959
    HE SPECIALIZED              
    IN FINDING LOST CHILDREN.   


160
00:14:36,776 --> 00:14:38,709
[ Frustrated Grunt ]            


161
00:14:38,778 --> 00:14:42,280
WHAT COULD POSSIBLY MAKE        
THIS TRIP MORE DEPRESSING?      


162
00:14:42,348 --> 00:14:44,715
    [ Sighs ]                   


163
00:14:50,789 --> 00:14:53,724
<i>[ Water Splashing ]</i>             
<i>[ Man Grunts, Laughs ]</i>          


164
00:14:53,793 --> 00:14:56,960
                OH, I'M THIRSTY.
                COME ON.        


165
00:14:58,431 --> 00:15:01,399
            SWEETHEART,         
            GO GET YOURSELF     
            ANOTHER HURRICANE.  


166
00:15:01,467 --> 00:15:03,967
            [ Coughs ]          
            HURRY BACK. GO, GO! 


167
00:15:04,036 --> 00:15:06,870
                    HURRY UP.   


168
00:15:06,939 --> 00:15:09,973
                MMM. AHH.       


169
00:15:18,651 --> 00:15:20,684
                    HEY.        


170
00:15:20,753 --> 00:15:22,753
            WHAT DO YOU WANT?   


171
00:15:24,023 --> 00:15:26,524
I CAME HERE TO KILL YOU.        


172
00:15:44,344 --> 00:15:46,678
WELL, THAT SHOULD WORK.         


173
00:15:47,814 --> 00:15:50,114
    BUT I'M GOING TO            
    NEED YOUR HELP.             


174
00:16:28,288 --> 00:16:30,955
        <i> [ Knocking On Door ]</i>   


175
00:16:31,024 --> 00:16:33,925
    YEAH. I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.  
    GOTTA GO.                   


176
00:16:33,994 --> 00:16:35,927
            STAY COOL.          


177
00:16:45,071 --> 00:16:48,906
<i>I'M TELLING YOU,</i>                
<i>I DON'T KNOW WHERE IT ALL WENT.</i> 
            <i> NO. LISTEN TO ME.</i>  


178
00:16:48,975 --> 00:16:51,976
                LISTEN TO ME!   
                I DON'T CARE    
                ABOUT EXCUSES.  


179
00:16:52,044 --> 00:16:55,045
            FOR $300 A NIGHT,   
            I WANT ICE!         


180
00:17:02,388 --> 00:17:04,388
        [ Both ]                
        HI!                     


181
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:16,900
            VERY FUNNY, SYDNEY. 


182
00:17:18,904 --> 00:17:21,038
    I'M SORRY?                  


183
00:17:21,107 --> 00:17:23,907
                THE CIGARETTES  
                THAT YOU LEFT   
                ON MY PILLOW.   


184
00:17:23,976 --> 00:17:27,211
I HAD NOTHING                   
TO DO WITH THAT.                


185
00:17:27,280 --> 00:17:30,948
            JAROD. YOU TOLD HIM 
            ABOUT THE PATCH,    
            DIDN'T YOU?         


186
00:17:31,017 --> 00:17:34,185
    I?                          
            [ Both ]            
            DOCTOR?             


187
00:17:34,254 --> 00:17:36,287
EXCUSE ME?                      
    WE DIDN'T REALIZE--         


188
00:17:36,356 --> 00:17:38,822
                THAT YOU'D      
                BE ATTENDING--  
    THE CONFERENCE.             


189
00:17:38,891 --> 00:17:40,892
EXCUSE ME.                      


190
00:17:40,960 --> 00:17:43,427
            I NEED              
            A VERY LARGE DRINK. 


191
00:17:43,496 --> 00:17:45,496
        DON'T YOU--             
                RECOGNIZE US?   


192
00:17:45,565 --> 00:17:47,698
    IT'S MILLIE PILCHER.        
            AND TILLIE PILCHER. 


193
00:17:47,767 --> 00:17:51,736
<i>-WE WERE PART OF THE WEEK-LONG--</i>
-INTERNATIONAL STUDY PROGRAM?   


194
00:17:51,804 --> 00:17:54,505
I'M AFRAID YOU'RE MISTAKING ME  
FOR SOMEONE ELSE.               


195
00:17:54,574 --> 00:17:56,507
    WE COULD NEVER--            
                FORGET YOU--    


196
00:17:56,576 --> 00:17:58,409
            [ Both ]            
            DR. JACOB.          


197
00:18:00,814 --> 00:18:02,747
<i>[ Sydney's Voice Echoing ]</i>      
<i>JACOB!</i>                          


198
00:18:02,815 --> 00:18:05,349
<i>[ Jacob's Voice Echoing ]</i>       
<i>SYDNEY!</i>                         


199
00:18:42,088 --> 00:18:46,090
WE'RE REALLY GONNA DO THIS.     
 WE'RE GONNA WHACK THIS GUY OUT.


200
00:18:46,159 --> 00:18:49,527
    NO, YOU'RE GONNA STAY HERE  
    AND WATCH THAT GATE.        


201
00:18:49,595 --> 00:18:53,831
    HEY, I CAME HERE            
    TO DO THE DEED,             
    NOT PLAY WATCHDOG.          


202
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:56,734
        NOW YOU LISTEN TO ME.   


203
00:18:56,802 --> 00:18:58,803
        THIS IS NOT             
        SOME FIELD TRIP...      


204
00:18:58,871 --> 00:19:03,140
    OR A CORRESPONDENCE COURSE  
    THAT YOU ORDER OFF THE BACK 
    OF A MATCH PACK.            


205
00:19:03,209 --> 00:19:06,010
            PEOPLE WILL DIE,    
            AND WHEN THEY DO,   


206
00:19:06,078 --> 00:19:09,680
        IT WILL BE DONE BY ME,  
        MY WAY,                 


207
00:19:09,749 --> 00:19:11,749
                ALONE.          


208
00:19:11,817 --> 00:19:14,586
                IS THAT CLEAR?  


209
00:19:15,555 --> 00:19:17,154
                IS THAT CLEAR?  


210
00:19:17,223 --> 00:19:20,958
DON'T HAVE TO                   
GET RUN OVER BY NO TRUCK        
TO GET OUT OF THE ROAD.         


211
00:20:10,443 --> 00:20:13,444
<i>[ Two Gunshots ]</i>                
<i>[ Thudding ]</i>                    


212
00:20:15,781 --> 00:20:19,116
            <i> [ Camera Shutter</i>   
              <i> Clicking ]</i>       


213
00:20:33,300 --> 00:20:36,667
        HE'S DEAD?              


214
00:20:36,736 --> 00:20:40,071
    - WHAT THE HELL             
      ARE YOU DOING UP HERE?    
    - I ASKED YOU A QUESTION.   


215
00:20:43,143 --> 00:20:45,209
            YEAH, HE'S DEAD.    


216
00:20:46,478 --> 00:20:49,813
EVERYTHING WENT, UM, SMOOTH?    


217
00:20:49,882 --> 00:20:53,050
            I DIDN'T HEAR       
            ANY COMPLAINING.    


218
00:20:53,119 --> 00:20:55,653
        HELP ME CARRY HIM       
        DOWNSTAIRS.             


219
00:20:55,722 --> 00:20:58,923
I WANNA SEE THE BODY.           


220
00:20:58,991 --> 00:21:01,525
            ARE YOU KIDDING ME? 
WHAT DO YOU THINK?              


221
00:21:18,244 --> 00:21:20,677
            NOW THE NEXT TIME   
            YOU GET THE URGE... 


222
00:21:20,746 --> 00:21:24,048
            TO STICK A GUN      
            IN MY FACE,         


223
00:21:24,117 --> 00:21:27,351
        YOU BETTER MAKE SURE    
         YOU PULL THE TRIGGER.  


224
00:21:28,588 --> 00:21:31,522
            <i> HELP ME CARRY HIM</i>  
            <i> DOWNSTAIRS.</i>        


225
00:21:41,567 --> 00:21:43,567
WHY ARE WE STOPPING?            


226
00:21:43,636 --> 00:21:47,471
                GONNA GET RID   
                OF THE PACKAGE. 


227
00:21:47,540 --> 00:21:51,876
HERE?                           
        UNCLE TUG'S FOND OF     
        FERTILIZING THIS FIELD. 


228
00:21:53,246 --> 00:21:55,579
    SHOVEL'S IN THE BACK.       


229
00:21:59,852 --> 00:22:02,653
JACOB SPENT THE NEXT SEVERAL    
MONTHS IN THE HOSPITAL.         


230
00:22:02,722 --> 00:22:05,889
        HE WAS EVENTUALLY       
        TRANSFERRED TO          
        A PRIVATE-CARE CLINIC.  


231
00:22:05,958 --> 00:22:08,059
    WHEN DID--                  
            THE ACCIDENT OCCUR? 


232
00:22:08,127 --> 00:22:11,261
            AUGUST 2, '67.      


233
00:22:17,837 --> 00:22:20,104
WOULD YOU--                     
                    EXCUSE US?  


234
00:22:20,173 --> 00:22:23,106
IT WAS NICE--                   
                MEETING YOU.    


235
00:22:38,525 --> 00:22:40,458
    THANKS FOR YOUR HELP.       


236
00:22:42,094 --> 00:22:45,095
YOU SHOOT 'EM,                  
 YOU BURY 'EM.                  


237
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:49,800
                    LET'S GO.   


238
00:23:07,186 --> 00:23:09,687
SOUVENIR                        
OF A DEAD MAN.                  


239
00:23:15,828 --> 00:23:19,130
    - DID YOU SEE IT HAPPEN?    
    - NOT EXACTLY.              


240
00:23:19,198 --> 00:23:21,131
NOT EXACTLY?                    


241
00:23:21,200 --> 00:23:23,967
        I SAW HIM PLANT THE GUY,
        BUT I WASN'T THERE      
        WHEN HE POPPED HIM.     


242
00:23:24,036 --> 00:23:26,804
    I WORK ALONE.               


243
00:23:26,873 --> 00:23:29,840
    THE PICTURES WILL GIVE YOU  
     THE UP CLOSE AND PERSONAL. 


244
00:23:29,909 --> 00:23:33,277
I'LL TAKE                       
THE DOUBLE PRINTS.              


245
00:23:33,346 --> 00:23:37,381
HERE'S OUR NEXT TARGET.         
THIS TIME I WANT IT SEEN        
WITH REAL EYES.                 


246
00:23:37,450 --> 00:23:39,783
<i>UNDERSTOOD?</i>                     


247
00:23:39,852 --> 00:23:41,852
        IT'S YOUR PARTY.        


248
00:23:45,458 --> 00:23:47,959
                HEY.            
                WHEN DO WE MOVE?


249
00:23:50,897 --> 00:23:53,831
    I'LL CALL YOU.              


250
00:23:53,899 --> 00:23:58,235
WHY DOES TUG BEAULIEU           
WANT YOU DEAD?                  
    THAT'S THE $64,000 QUESTION.


251
00:23:58,304 --> 00:24:01,072
HE'S ONLY PAYING ME 50.         


252
00:24:01,140 --> 00:24:04,308
            HEY. PUT YOURSELF   
            IN MY SHOES.        


253
00:24:04,377 --> 00:24:07,210
    YOU BREAK INTO MY HOUSE.    
     YOU PUT A GUN TO MY NECK.  


254
00:24:07,280 --> 00:24:09,680
        YOU TELL ME SOMEBODY'S  
        GONNA KILL ME.          


255
00:24:09,749 --> 00:24:13,917
    THEN YOU FAKE MY MURDER,    
    YOU BURY ME, AND YOU GIVE ME
    A STRAW TO BREATHE THROUGH. 


256
00:24:13,986 --> 00:24:17,087
- YOUR POINT?                   
- THE POINT IS I DON'T EVEN KNOW
  WHO THE HELL YOU ARE!         


257
00:24:17,156 --> 00:24:20,758
MY NAME IS JAROD.               
WHY DOES TUG BEAULIEU           
WANT YOU DEAD?                  


258
00:24:22,561 --> 00:24:25,162
            BUSINESS CONFLICTS. 


259
00:24:25,231 --> 00:24:27,564
CONFLICTS?                      


260
00:24:27,633 --> 00:24:30,801
        I OWN SOME JAZZ CLUBS.  
        BEAULIEU WANTED         
        TO BUY ME OUT.          


261
00:24:30,870 --> 00:24:34,071
            I WASN'T INTERESTED.
HE'S WILLING TO KILL            
FOR THOSE CLUBS?                


262
00:24:34,140 --> 00:24:37,374
    THE QUARTER'S A SMALL PLACE,
    BUT THE LAND'S INVALUABLE.  


263
00:24:38,844 --> 00:24:41,445
            WAIT A SECOND.      
            WHERE ARE YOU GOING?


264
00:24:41,514 --> 00:24:46,149
LOOK, YOU'RE NOT                
THE ONLY PERSON THAT BEAULIEU   
HAS A MURDER CONTRACT ON.       


265
00:24:47,186 --> 00:24:50,921
                    OH, MY GOD. 
WHAT?                           


266
00:24:50,989 --> 00:24:52,990
            [ Sighs ]           
            THAT'S MY WIFE.     


267
00:24:53,058 --> 00:24:56,226
Y-YOUR WIFE?                    
B-BUT YOU WERE                  
IN THE POOL WITH--              


268
00:24:56,295 --> 00:25:00,264
            SEPARATED. WE'RE IN 
            A HEALING PERIOD.   


269
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:04,168
    SHE RUNS ONE OF THE CLUBS.  
    I RUN THE OTHER ONE.        


270
00:25:04,237 --> 00:25:08,672
DON'T ANSWER THE PHONE,         
AND DON'T GO IN THE BATHROOM.   


271
00:25:08,741 --> 00:25:11,675
    WELL, WAIT A MINUTE.        
    SUPPOSING I GOTTA, YOU KNOW?


272
00:25:11,744 --> 00:25:13,944
        I AIN'T GOIN' IN THIS.  


273
00:25:15,581 --> 00:25:17,814
        [ Sighs ]               
        COME HERE.              


274
00:25:25,991 --> 00:25:28,092
                    WHO THE HELL
                    IS THAT?    


275
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:32,162
THAT'S THE GUY                  
THAT WAS REALLY                 
GOING TO KILL YOU.              


276
00:25:32,232 --> 00:25:36,334
            UM... ICE BUCKET    
            WILL BE JUST FINE.  


277
00:25:36,402 --> 00:25:38,335
    GOOD.                       


278
00:25:44,009 --> 00:25:47,944
        I'VE HAD THE BUILDING   
        ON THE MARKET           
        A COUPLE OF YEARS.      


279
00:25:48,014 --> 00:25:50,514
HAVEN'T HAD MUCH INTEREST       
SINCE MR. HERBERT WENT AWAY.    


280
00:25:57,289 --> 00:26:00,190
        <i> I'D HAVE CLEARED OUT</i>   
        <i> THE REST OF THIS JUNK,</i> 


281
00:26:00,259 --> 00:26:02,927
            BUT I'M JUST GONNA  
            BLOW THE PLACE UP   
            AND SELL THE LAND.  


282
00:26:02,996 --> 00:26:05,562
I'M SURE GLAD YOU DIDN'T.       
DO YOU MIND IF I TAKE A LOOK?   


283
00:26:05,632 --> 00:26:07,564
                    MM-MMM.     


284
00:26:07,634 --> 00:26:10,367
        SO YOU SAY YOU'RE ONE   
        OF THOSE KIDS SONNY     
        WAS LOOKIN' FOR?        


285
00:26:10,435 --> 00:26:12,569
        I DON'T KNOW.           


286
00:26:12,638 --> 00:26:15,339
I WAS HOPING THERE WAS SOMETHING
THAT MR. HERBERT HAD HERE...    


287
00:26:15,408 --> 00:26:18,542
THAT WOULD HELP ME              
FIND MY PARENTS.                


288
00:26:18,611 --> 00:26:21,112
<i>YOU SAID</i>                        
<i>THERE WERE SOME OTHER MEN</i>       
<i>THAT CAME LOOKING FOR HIM?</i>      


289
00:26:21,180 --> 00:26:23,280
        JUST FORE               
        MR. HERBERT DISAPPEARED.


290
00:26:23,349 --> 00:26:25,749
            THEY CLAIMED        
            HE OWED THEM MONEY. 


291
00:26:25,818 --> 00:26:29,320
    TELL THE TRUTH,             
    THEY LOOKED LIKE            
    VENDING MACHINES WITH HEADS.


292
00:26:29,388 --> 00:26:32,656
            [ Chuckles ]        
            SO I DIDN'T ASK     
            TOO MANY QUESTIONS. 


293
00:26:32,725 --> 00:26:35,559
            OH, THERE WAS       
            A WEIRD-LOOKING ONE 
            WITH AN OXYGEN TANK.


294
00:26:37,497 --> 00:26:40,230
        - OXYGEN TANK?          
        - YEAH.                 


295
00:26:40,299 --> 00:26:43,868
            SPOOKY-LOOKING GUY. 
            HAD DEEP-SET EYES.  
            YOU KNOW HIM?       


296
00:26:43,936 --> 00:26:46,837
WE'VE MET.                      
DID THEY TAKE ANYTHING?         


297
00:26:46,906 --> 00:26:48,906
            THEY WAS IN         
            A PRETTY BIG HURRY. 


298
00:26:48,974 --> 00:26:53,043
    I NEVER GOT A CHANCE        
    TO TELL 'EM ABOUT THE STUFF 
    DOWN IN THE BASEMENT.       


299
00:26:53,112 --> 00:26:55,045
    THE BASEMENT?               


300
00:26:55,114 --> 00:26:57,681
    <i> A DOZEN BOXES</i>              
    <i> FULL OF FILES AND PHOTOS.</i>  


301
00:26:57,750 --> 00:27:00,283
                <i> MOSTLY THEY'RE</i> 
                <i> MISSING KIDS.</i>  


302
00:27:06,559 --> 00:27:09,793
        IS THIS ALL THERE IS?   
THAT'S IT.                      


303
00:27:09,862 --> 00:27:13,129
                IT'S NOT HERE.  
NOTHIN' ABOUT                   
YOUR PARENTS?                   


304
00:27:13,198 --> 00:27:17,534
        THESE FILES, THEY ONLY  
        GO BACK 20 YEARS.       
OH, I'M SORRY.                  


305
00:27:19,839 --> 00:27:21,739
        I'M NOT HERE.           


306
00:27:21,808 --> 00:27:25,075
            I'M NOT HERE!       


307
00:27:25,144 --> 00:27:29,313
        [ Sighs, Panting ]      


308
00:27:29,382 --> 00:27:33,116
            I'M NOT HERE.       
            [ Sighs ]           


309
00:27:42,094 --> 00:27:44,595
            I'M NOT... HERE.    


310
00:27:49,235 --> 00:27:51,768
<i>[ Thunderclap ]</i>                 
GET YOUR MIND OFF OF YOUR CAREER
FOR ONE SECOND, WILL YOU?       


311
00:27:51,837 --> 00:27:53,837
    I'M TALKING                 
    ABOUT THE CHILDREN.         


312
00:27:53,906 --> 00:27:56,539
    WHAT'S SO TROUBLING         
    ABOUT CHILDREN,             
    FOR GOD'S SAKES?            


313
00:27:56,608 --> 00:28:00,177
- DO YOU KNOW HOW               
  WE GOT THOSE CHILDREN?        
- I KNOW WHAT I NEED TO KNOW.   


314
00:28:00,246 --> 00:28:02,345
NO, NO. YOU KNOW WHAT           
THE CENTRE WANTS YOU TO KNOW.   


315
00:28:02,414 --> 00:28:04,815
<i>YOU-- YOU ALWAYS DO THIS.</i>       


316
00:28:04,884 --> 00:28:07,918
YOU ALWAYS PUSH AWAY            
WHAT DOESN'T FIT INTO YOUR      
PRISTINE VIEW OF THE WORLD.     


317
00:28:07,987 --> 00:28:10,754
- ALL YOU WANT TO DO IS POISON  
  THE GOOD THINGS IN YOUR LIFE. 
- SYDNEY!                       


318
00:28:10,823 --> 00:28:12,823
<i>[ Honking, Crashing ]</i>           


319
00:28:20,032 --> 00:28:22,299
        <i> [ Knocking On Door ]</i>   


320
00:28:22,367 --> 00:28:24,367
        [ Whispers ]            
        JACOB.                  


321
00:28:26,839 --> 00:28:28,772
    [ Simultaneously ]          
    WE HAVE TO TALK.            


322
00:28:34,546 --> 00:28:37,548
    I DON'T WANNA RUIN YOUR FUN,
    BUT HOW LONG YOU PLAN ON    
    KEEPIN' HIM IN HERE?        


323
00:28:37,617 --> 00:28:40,618
I DON'T KNOW. I'VE GROWN        
SORT OF ATTACHED TO HIM.        


324
00:28:45,157 --> 00:28:47,491
            THAT'S A SICK MAN.  


325
00:28:51,230 --> 00:28:53,197
                <i> I LIKE IT HERE.</i>


326
00:28:53,265 --> 00:28:56,600
                    PEACEFUL.   
                    QUIET.      


327
00:28:56,668 --> 00:29:00,070
THE BUILDING MANAGER TOLD ME    
THAT YOU WORKED FOR SONNY       
FOR THE LAST 10 YEARS.          


328
00:29:00,139 --> 00:29:02,072
                    ELEVEN.     
                    [ Chuckles ]


329
00:29:02,141 --> 00:29:06,476
        HE PUT AN AD            
        IN A LOCAL PAPER AND    
        MISSPELLED A FEW WORDS. 


330
00:29:06,545 --> 00:29:08,545
            I TOOK PITY ON HIM. 


331
00:29:10,349 --> 00:29:12,850
                WHAT YOU WANT   
                WITH HIM ANYWAY?


332
00:29:14,720 --> 00:29:16,720
WHEN I WAS A LITTLE BOY,        


333
00:29:16,788 --> 00:29:21,157
I WAS... SEPARATED              
FROM MY PARENTS.                


334
00:29:21,227 --> 00:29:24,261
I BELIEVE THEY MIGHT            
HAVE HIRED MR. HERBERT          
TO FIND ME.                     


335
00:29:24,329 --> 00:29:27,698
        YOU CHECK ALL THE FILES?
THEY DON'T DATE BACK            
FAR ENOUGH.                     


336
00:29:27,766 --> 00:29:30,000
I NEED TO SPEAK                 
TO SONNY PERSONALLY.            


337
00:29:30,069 --> 00:29:33,336
            THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.  
WHY IS THAT?                    


338
00:29:33,405 --> 00:29:35,439
            HE'S IN A HOSPITAL. 


339
00:29:35,507 --> 00:29:38,275
                BURNS OVER 80%  
                OF HIS BODY.    


340
00:29:39,912 --> 00:29:43,180
            POLICE SAY          
            IT WAS AN ACCIDENT. 
            FELL ASLEEP SMOKING.


341
00:29:43,248 --> 00:29:45,482
YOU DON'T SOUND CONVINCED.      


342
00:29:45,551 --> 00:29:48,018
        SONNY WAS AN INSOMNIAC. 


343
00:29:48,087 --> 00:29:51,655
    HE'D NEVER HAVE             
    FALLEN ASLEEP SO DEEP THAT  
    HE'D SET HIMSELF AFIRE.     


344
00:29:51,724 --> 00:29:54,225
                I TRIED TO TELL 
                THE POLICE,     


345
00:29:54,293 --> 00:29:57,360
        BUT THERE'S NO RECORD   
        OF HIS PROBLEM,         


346
00:29:57,430 --> 00:30:00,030
            SO THEY LET IT GO.  


347
00:30:00,099 --> 00:30:02,399
THERE'S SOMETHING ELSE.         


348
00:30:02,468 --> 00:30:05,069
        SONNY THOUGHT           
        HE WAS BEING FOLLOWED.  


349
00:30:05,137 --> 00:30:08,405
            AFTER HE GOT HURT,  
            I GOT SCARED.       


350
00:30:09,942 --> 00:30:11,874
WHERE IS HE NOW?                


351
00:30:11,944 --> 00:30:14,210
        V.A. HOSPITAL, SLIDELL. 


352
00:30:18,917 --> 00:30:21,751
AFTER WE SPOKE EARLIER--        
        WE BOTH HAD THE SAME--  


353
00:30:21,820 --> 00:30:24,154
THOUGHT ABOUT YOUR--            
                    ACCIDENT.   


354
00:30:25,824 --> 00:30:27,758
        YES?                    


355
00:30:27,826 --> 00:30:30,059
        YOU SAID THE ACCIDENT   
        WAS ON--                


356
00:30:30,128 --> 00:30:32,663
            AUGUST 2--          
                        1967?   


357
00:30:33,965 --> 00:30:36,232
    <i> - THE LAST TIME WE SAW--</i>   
     - DR. JACOB--              


358
00:30:36,301 --> 00:30:38,701
WAS ON THE MONDAY BEFORE.       


359
00:30:38,770 --> 00:30:42,038
<i>AND YOU CAN BOTH REMEMBER</i>       
<i>A SPECIFIC MONDAY...</i>            


360
00:30:42,107 --> 00:30:44,507
<i>30 YEARS AGO?</i>                   


361
00:30:44,576 --> 00:30:47,744
IT WAS THE DAY BEFORE           
OUR 10th--                      
                    BIRTHDAY.   


362
00:30:47,813 --> 00:30:51,881
            AND THE FIRST TIME  
            WE'D EVER SEEN--    
        [ Both ] A GUN.         


363
00:30:53,919 --> 00:30:56,586
<i>DR. JACOB WAS SHOUTING.</i>         
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>AT YOU?</i>                         


364
00:30:56,655 --> 00:31:00,690
            OH, NO,             
            BUT IT WAS A VERY-- 
LOUD ARGUMENT.                  


365
00:31:00,758 --> 00:31:04,761
<i>THE OTHER MAN SAID--</i>            
            <i> "IF YOU'RE NOT PART</i>
             <i> OF THE SOLUTION"--</i>


366
00:31:04,830 --> 00:31:07,063
<i>"THEN YOU'RE PART</i>               
<i> OF THE PROBLEM."</i>               


367
00:31:07,132 --> 00:31:10,032
        <i> THEN DR. JACOB BEGAN--</i> 
<i>TO ARGUE BACK.</i>                  


368
00:31:10,101 --> 00:31:12,102
AND THAT'S WHEN--               


369
00:31:13,105 --> 00:31:15,038
        HE PRESSED THE GUN...   


370
00:31:15,107 --> 00:31:17,541
        <i> INTO DR. JACOB'S NECK.</i> 


371
00:31:21,513 --> 00:31:23,479
<i>DR. BILLY.</i>                      
                        <i> YES.</i>   


372
00:31:23,548 --> 00:31:26,316
                    <i> DR. BILLY.</i> 
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>BILLY?</i>                          


373
00:31:28,019 --> 00:31:30,319
    YOU MEAN                    
    DR. WILLIAM RAINES.         


374
00:31:30,388 --> 00:31:34,591
<i>[ Simultaneously ]</i>              
<i>DR. BILLY SCARED US TO DEATH.</i>   


375
00:32:25,344 --> 00:32:27,344
<i>[ Knocking ]</i>                    


376
00:32:47,732 --> 00:32:49,666
            [ Grunts ]          


377
00:32:49,735 --> 00:32:51,735
                SON OF A BITCH! 


378
00:32:57,876 --> 00:32:59,876
            [ Grunts ]          


379
00:33:12,124 --> 00:33:16,126
        NOW I'M GOING TO FORGET 
        YOU JUST DID THAT,      


380
00:33:18,163 --> 00:33:22,165
    AND IT WOULD BE             
    DISRESPECTFUL TO KILL YOU   
    IN FRONT OF FAMILY.         


381
00:33:24,869 --> 00:33:26,870
            WHERE'S             
            BEN WORTH'S BODY?   


382
00:33:26,939 --> 00:33:29,071
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>IS THAT WHY YOU'RE HERE?</i>        


383
00:33:30,642 --> 00:33:34,076
<i>I MOVED HIM.</i>                    


384
00:33:34,145 --> 00:33:37,013
JUST IN CASE HOTSHOT HERE       
STARTED MOUTHIN' OFF...         


385
00:33:37,081 --> 00:33:39,349
AND SOMEBODY WENT LOOKING,      


386
00:33:39,417 --> 00:33:41,417
YOU'D BE PROTECTED.             


387
00:33:41,486 --> 00:33:44,554
    - NOT THAT YOU'D DO         
      SOMETHING LIKE THAT.      
    - WHAT ABOUT THE WOMAN?     


388
00:33:44,622 --> 00:33:49,025
- I SAW YOU GO TO HER HOUSE,    
  AND YOU NEVER CAME OUT.       
- YOU'VE BEEN A BUSY BOY.       


389
00:33:50,262 --> 00:33:53,096
    WE ALL HAVE QUIRKS.         


390
00:33:53,164 --> 00:33:56,199
<i>MINE HAPPENS TO BE</i>              
<i>TAKING PHOTOS, AS YOU KNOW.</i>     


391
00:33:56,267 --> 00:34:00,703
BUT EVEN THAT GETS BORING,      
SO I DECIDED TO TAKE            
SOME LIVE ONES.                 


392
00:34:02,541 --> 00:34:06,109
NOW WHAT DID I TELL YOU         
ABOUT POINTING GUNS AT ME?      


393
00:34:06,177 --> 00:34:08,478
                    PUT IT UP.  


394
00:34:23,328 --> 00:34:25,595
                SHE STILL ALIVE?
<i>FOR THE TIME BEING.</i>             


395
00:34:25,664 --> 00:34:29,399
I'M GOING TO DO HER             
IN FRONT OF YOU.                


396
00:34:29,468 --> 00:34:33,836
<i>I KNOW THIS LITTLE SPOT</i>         
<i>IN THE WOODS</i>                    
<i>NOT TOO FAR FROM HERE.</i>          


397
00:34:33,905 --> 00:34:37,507
PERFECT PLACE FOR A WOMAN       
WHO'S BEEN ABANDONED            
BY HER HUSBAND...               


398
00:34:37,575 --> 00:34:41,010
<i>TO PARK HER CAR,</i>                
<i>ROLL UP THE WINDOW...</i>           


399
00:34:41,079 --> 00:34:42,913
    AND GAS HERSELF.            


400
00:34:42,981 --> 00:34:46,649
    YEAH. I KNEW YOU WERE       
    THE RIGHT MAN FOR THE JOB.  


401
00:34:49,588 --> 00:34:52,756
        - WAIT A MINUTE.        
        - WHAT?                 


402
00:34:52,824 --> 00:34:56,993
    STORY ON THE LIMP IS        
    YOU TOOK ONE RUNNING        
    FROM THE COPS IN CHICAGO.   


403
00:34:57,062 --> 00:35:00,496
            DOCTORS HAD TO TAKE 
            AN INCH OF BONE OUT.
            TRUE?               


404
00:35:00,565 --> 00:35:03,933
        - YEAH, IT'S TRUE.      
        - SHOW ME.              


405
00:35:05,504 --> 00:35:07,504
         - WHAT?                
        <i> - [ Gun Cocks ]</i>        


406
00:35:07,572 --> 00:35:09,506
            SHOW ME YOUR KNEE.  


407
00:35:28,594 --> 00:35:30,860
<i>IS THERE ANYTHING ELSE</i>          
<i>YOU'D LIKE TO SEE?</i>              


408
00:35:30,929 --> 00:35:33,129
                    NAH.        


409
00:35:33,197 --> 00:35:35,131
                LET'S GO.       


410
00:35:36,568 --> 00:35:39,201
I GOTTA USE THE CAN.            


411
00:35:42,374 --> 00:35:44,707
                <i> [ Beaulieu ]</i>   
                <i> DONNY!</i>         


412
00:35:47,379 --> 00:35:49,812
                        NO.     


413
00:35:49,881 --> 00:35:52,415
        WE'VE BOTHERED MR. DOE  
        ENOUGH FOR ONE DAY.     


414
00:35:52,483 --> 00:35:55,485
        I'M NOT GONNA LET YOU   
        FOUL UP HIS HOTEL ROOM  
        ON TOP OF IT.           


415
00:35:56,822 --> 00:35:58,822
                <i> NOW LET'S GO.</i>  


416
00:36:14,238 --> 00:36:16,872
        [ Deep Sigh ]           


417
00:37:24,642 --> 00:37:27,476
SO, JAROD,                      
IS EVERYTHING SET?              


418
00:37:29,047 --> 00:37:31,480
            COPS WILL THINK     
            SHE KILLED HERSELF, 


419
00:37:31,549 --> 00:37:34,317
            DEPRESSED ABOUT     
            THE DISAPPEARANCE   
            OF HER HUSBAND...   


420
00:37:34,386 --> 00:37:36,386
        AND THE FAILED BUSINESS.


421
00:37:36,454 --> 00:37:39,555
[ Chuckles ]                    
THAT'S JUST FINE.               


422
00:37:39,624 --> 00:37:41,624
            NOW ABOUT MY MONEY. 


423
00:37:41,693 --> 00:37:45,128
    - WELL, UH, GOT             
      A LITTLE PROBLEM THERE.   
    - WHAT KIND OF PROBLEM?     


424
00:37:45,196 --> 00:37:49,165
    - THIS KIND.                
    - NOW YOU KNOW WHY NOTHIN'  
      EVER LANDS ON MY DOORSTEP.


425
00:37:49,234 --> 00:37:52,601
        - DO HIM.               
        - A PLEASURE.           


426
00:37:52,670 --> 00:37:54,537
                    BIG MISTAKE.


427
00:37:57,676 --> 00:38:00,676
                YOU NEVER LEARN,
                DO YOU?         


428
00:38:00,745 --> 00:38:02,745
                        DORIS.  


429
00:38:04,149 --> 00:38:07,283
<i>[ Ben ]</i>                         
<i>COME HERE, BABY. COME HERE.</i>     


430
00:38:11,222 --> 00:38:13,989
    - GET IN.                   
    - HOW MUCH YOU WANT?        


431
00:38:14,058 --> 00:38:17,793
HOW MUCH DOES HE WANT?          
YOU WERE GONNA KILL MY WIFE.    
THINK YOU CAN BUY YOUR WAY OUT? 


432
00:38:17,862 --> 00:38:20,396
            ALL RIGHT, BEN.     
            THAT'S ENOUGH.      
            HE GETS THE POINT.  


433
00:38:20,464 --> 00:38:22,398
                    YEAH, RIGHT.


434
00:38:22,467 --> 00:38:24,968
                GET IN, OR DIE. 


435
00:38:28,907 --> 00:38:31,408
            YOU TOO, SQUIRRELLY.
            GET IN.             


436
00:38:38,316 --> 00:38:42,318
        WELL, I THINK IT'S TIME 
        FOR MY LAST PHOTO SHOOT.


437
00:38:46,958 --> 00:38:50,760
    NOW, I'M GONNA ASK YOU TWO  
    SOME QUESTIONS.             


438
00:38:50,829 --> 00:38:54,463
        YOU ANSWER CORRECTLY,   
        THIS'LL BE OVER SOON.   


439
00:38:59,270 --> 00:39:01,638
                DID YOU HIRE    
                AN ASSASSIN...  


440
00:39:01,706 --> 00:39:03,706
            TO KILL             
            BEN AND DORIS WORTH?


441
00:39:03,775 --> 00:39:07,276
    <i> I SAW YOUR LEG!</i>            
     <i> I SEEN THAT SCAR ON THERE!</i>


442
00:39:14,385 --> 00:39:16,318
            IT'S NEAT, HUH?     


443
00:39:16,387 --> 00:39:20,623
    A LITTLE MORTICIAN'S WAX,   
    A LITTLE PANCAKE MAKEUP,    
    AND VOILÀ.                  


444
00:39:20,692 --> 00:39:24,093
        NOW, DID YOU CONTRACT   
        FOR THE KILLING         
        OF BEN AND DORIS WORTH? 


445
00:39:27,131 --> 00:39:29,765
        I'M AFRAID THAT'S NOT   
        GONNA DO YOU ANY GOOD.  


446
00:39:29,834 --> 00:39:32,535
        AND I WOULDN'T TRY      
        SMASHING THE WINDOW.    


447
00:39:35,173 --> 00:39:38,941
            SHATTERPROOF GLASS. 


448
00:39:39,010 --> 00:39:43,679
<i>WELL, LOOKS TO ME LIKE</i>          
<i>YOU BOYS AREN'T INTERESTED</i>      
<i>IN DOING TOO MUCH TALKING, SO--</i> 


449
00:39:55,193 --> 00:39:57,993
        [ Both Coughing ]       


450
00:39:58,062 --> 00:40:00,329
                <i> THE EXHAUST!</i>   


451
00:40:04,635 --> 00:40:08,104
            <i> [ Jarod ]</i>          
            <i> HEY, GOOD LUCK</i>     
            <i> TO THE BOTH OF YOU.</i>


452
00:40:11,509 --> 00:40:14,544
<i>OKAY, HE HIRED YOU TO KILL 'EM,</i> 
<i>TO KILL ALL OF 'EM!</i>             


453
00:40:14,612 --> 00:40:17,313
    - DONNY!                    
    - I COULD TELL YOU WHERE    
      HE BURIED THE BODIES!     


454
00:40:17,382 --> 00:40:21,250
- I CAN'T HEAR YOU.             
- ALL RIGHT, JAROD. I DID IT.   


455
00:40:21,319 --> 00:40:24,620
    ALL RIGHT, JAROD,           
    I'LL GIVE YOU $100,000      
    TO OPEN THIS DOOR!          


456
00:40:26,057 --> 00:40:28,291
        MY, THAT'S AN AWFUL LOT 
        OF MONEY.               


457
00:40:28,359 --> 00:40:31,494
A MAN WOULD BE CRAZY            
NOT TO THINK THAT OFFER OVER.   


458
00:40:42,173 --> 00:40:44,841
<i>[ Coughing Continues ]</i>          


459
00:40:47,879 --> 00:40:50,479
        I THOUGHT IT OVER.      


460
00:40:50,548 --> 00:40:52,548
            NO DEAL.            


461
00:40:53,885 --> 00:40:56,118
            JAROD!              


462
00:40:57,588 --> 00:41:01,657
<i>- [ Coughing ]</i>                  
- YOU'RE JUST GONNA LET 'EM DIE?


463
00:41:01,726 --> 00:41:04,493
    I ONLY PUT ENOUGH GAS       
    IN THE TANK TO SCARE THEM.  


464
00:41:04,562 --> 00:41:07,663
    <i> THE ENGINE SHOULD SHUT OFF</i> 
    <i> IN ABOUT 30 SECONDS.</i>       


465
00:41:07,732 --> 00:41:10,867
I WISH I COULD STICK AROUND     
TO SEE HOW THEY TRY TO EXPLAIN  
THAT TAPE TO THE POLICE.        


466
00:41:10,935 --> 00:41:13,536
        THEY SHOULD BE HERE     
        ANY MINUTE.             


467
00:41:13,605 --> 00:41:15,838
        HEY, WHO COULD I SAY?   
        THANKS, PAL.            


468
00:41:15,907 --> 00:41:17,840
THANK YOU.                      


469
00:41:24,615 --> 00:41:29,251
YOU TWO, YOU WORK WELL TOGETHER.
 YOU SHOULD CONSIDER A MERGER.  


470
00:41:29,320 --> 00:41:32,522
SEE?                            
                OH, PLEASE,     
                DON'T START.    


471
00:41:37,195 --> 00:41:39,195
        I MISS YOU, JACOB.      


472
00:41:44,469 --> 00:41:46,970
    <i> AND I'VE MISSED YOU TOO,</i>   
    <i> SYDNEY.</i>                    


473
00:41:49,975 --> 00:41:52,675
            WHY HAS IT          
            TAKEN YOU SO LONG   
            TO TALK TO ME?      


474
00:41:52,744 --> 00:41:54,810
    I WAS AFRAID.               


475
00:41:54,879 --> 00:41:58,214
I THOUGHT THAT, UM,             


476
00:41:58,283 --> 00:42:01,117
IF I TRIED AND FAILED,          


477
00:42:01,185 --> 00:42:03,185
YOU'D BE GONE FOREVER.          


478
00:42:03,254 --> 00:42:07,156
JACOB... THAT NIGHT             
IN THE CAR--                    


479
00:42:07,225 --> 00:42:10,326
        I'VE ALREADY TOLD YOU,  
        SYDNEY.                 


480
00:42:10,395 --> 00:42:12,394
        IT WASN'T YOUR FAULT.   


481
00:42:14,966 --> 00:42:17,700
    BUT YOU SEE,                
    I WASN'T LISTENING...       


482
00:42:17,769 --> 00:42:21,604
    TO WHAT YOU WERE REALLY     
    TRYING TO SAY TO ME.        


483
00:42:21,673 --> 00:42:25,308
    YOU WERE IN TROUBLE.        
     YOU NEEDED MY HELP.        


484
00:42:25,376 --> 00:42:27,377
                I WAS...        


485
00:42:29,447 --> 00:42:31,447
                ASHAMED.        


486
00:42:33,951 --> 00:42:37,820
            I COULDN'T TELL YOU 
            WHAT I'D DONE,      


487
00:42:37,889 --> 00:42:39,822
                THE THINGS--    


488
00:42:39,891 --> 00:42:43,693
<i>JACOB, DID RAINES</i>               
<i>HAVE ANYTHING TO DO...</i>          


489
00:42:43,762 --> 00:42:47,463
WITH WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU,      
TO US?                          


490
00:42:47,532 --> 00:42:51,100
            YOU KNOW THE ANSWER 
            TO THAT, SYDNEY.    


491
00:42:51,169 --> 00:42:55,104
<i>[ Knocking, Door Opens ]</i>        
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>                 
<i>SYDNEY.</i>                         


492
00:42:55,173 --> 00:42:57,173
    YOU READY TO GO?            


493
00:42:59,678 --> 00:43:01,610
    DON'T SAY A WORD.           


494
00:43:15,693 --> 00:43:17,894
<i>[ Machinery Hissing ]</i>           
<i>[ Monitor Beeping ]</i>             


495
00:43:17,962 --> 00:43:20,462
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>YOU CAN TRY TO SPEAK</i>            
<i>TO MR. HERBERT,</i>                 


496
00:43:20,531 --> 00:43:24,199
        <i> BUT SINCE THE ACCIDENT,</i>
        <i> HE DRIFTS IN AND OUT</i>   
        <i> OF CONSCIOUSNESS.</i>      


497
00:43:45,757 --> 00:43:47,690
MR. HERBERT.                    


498
00:43:49,026 --> 00:43:51,327
<i>MR. HERBERT.</i>                    
        [ Quiet Moan ]          


499
00:43:52,597 --> 00:43:55,131
    SONNY.                      


500
00:43:55,200 --> 00:43:58,801
        [ Grunts ]              
<i>MY NAME IS JAROD.</i>               


501
00:43:58,870 --> 00:44:02,137
MR. HERBERT, 30 YEARS AGO,      


502
00:44:02,206 --> 00:44:05,575
MY PARENTS MAY HAVE             
HIRED YOU TO FIND ME.           


503
00:44:05,643 --> 00:44:07,810
YOU WERE                        
A PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR.         


504
00:44:07,879 --> 00:44:10,379
YOU USED TO HELP FIND           
LOST CHILDREN.                  


505
00:44:11,449 --> 00:44:13,248
        CH-CHILDREN.            


506
00:44:13,317 --> 00:44:17,620
    MR. HERBERT.                
    M-M-MR. HERBERT.            


507
00:44:17,689 --> 00:44:19,755
DO YOU RECOGNIZE THIS WOMAN?    


508
00:44:21,659 --> 00:44:25,427
THIS IS MY MOTHER.              
            OH.                 


509
00:44:27,064 --> 00:44:29,732
DO YOU REMEMBER HER NAME?       


510
00:44:30,768 --> 00:44:32,702
                NICE... WOMAN.  


511
00:44:34,605 --> 00:44:38,507
    WANTED TO FIND...           
    HER LITTLE BOY.             


512
00:44:38,576 --> 00:44:41,611
    YES. THAT'S RIGHT.          


513
00:44:41,679 --> 00:44:44,713
DO YOU REMEMBER                 
HER NAME?                       


514
00:44:44,782 --> 00:44:48,950
MR. HERBERT.                    
MR. HERBERT, DO YOU             
REMEMBER HER NAME?              


515
00:44:53,224 --> 00:44:55,224
        [ Sighs ]               


516
00:45:00,130 --> 00:45:04,800
[ Sighs ]                       
REMEMBER HER NAME.              


517
00:45:18,983 --> 00:45:21,817
            [ Rings ]           


518
00:45:24,054 --> 00:45:26,289
    HELLO.                      
        [ Jarod ]               
        HELLO, SYDNEY.          


519
00:45:26,357 --> 00:45:28,290
    JAROD.                      


520
00:45:28,358 --> 00:45:31,260
        I WANTED TO THANK YOU   
        FOR SENDING ME          
        THE PHOTOGRAPH.         


521
00:45:31,329 --> 00:45:33,229
WHAT PHOTOGRAPH, JAROD?         


522
00:45:33,298 --> 00:45:35,298
SONNY HERBERT.                  


523
00:45:36,701 --> 00:45:40,670
JAROD, I DID NOT                
SEND YOU ANY PHOTOS.            


524
00:45:40,738 --> 00:45:44,139
IN FACT, I WAS JUST ABOUT       
TO THANK YOU...                 


525
00:45:44,208 --> 00:45:48,176
FOR THE MESSAGE                 
LETTING ME KNOW ABOUT           
THE TWINS CONVENTION.           


526
00:45:49,447 --> 00:45:51,880
        SYDNEY,                 


527
00:45:51,949 --> 00:45:54,450
    I DIDN'T SEND YOU           
    ANY MESSAGE.                


528
00:45:58,288 --> 00:46:00,222
        THEN WHO DID?           


529
00:46:44,969 --> 00:46:45,968
            [ Mews ]            


